President Biden expressed his concern about the decline in federal investment in science and technology over the past 30 years. He emphasized the importance of such investments in maintaining the country's safety, security, and health. He also urged leaders to be cautious about spreading misinformation related to health crises, as people's lives are at stake. Additionally, he highlighted the need for healthcare workers to reflect the diversity of the communities they serve. President Biden expressed his interest in artificial intelligence (AI) and its potential to transform research, while also acknowledging the risks associated with it. He announced plans for executive action and bipartisan legislation to ensure responsible AI innovation. The President also emphasized the importance of high-quality healthcare for all Americans and announced investments in patient safety and the development of antibiotics. He stressed the need to reduce medical errors and improve health outcomes. President Biden called for funding the government to avoid potential impacts on science, health, and other vital areas.